caption: I love this place, I ate here once and I go here regularly now. If your in the neighborhood, you have to give it a try!
Hands down best doner in Chicago! Took us a a long time to find one. The 40 minute drive is definitely worth it. Great service and extremely clean which is always a huge thing for me.
I have been searching for a taste of real European kebab for a long time. I finally found it here. Absolutely delicious food, nice and friendly service. I'll be coming back.

Not sure what the hype is about. Sandwich was OK at best. Too much “coleslaw” and not enough meat. Fries could have used less salt. Seemed like an enhanced, halal Subway — better options in other places. When I asked for a tea, the owner/operator/cool said, “I am busy, I don’t have time right now”. Okay, then.
I eat in this spot a lot since I work nearby. I like how the service is always excellent and they keep the spot well organized constantly. Prices are fair and they serve big portions.

The certified danks. Fries, check. Doner, check. Sauce, check.

Best Döner in town. As simple as that.
amazing food just like back home

What isn't their to say about Ali Baba Doener. It's absolutely delightful and better than any of the Doener I've ever had in Europe (including in Germany). Absolutely superb, delicious, and worth every penny. Swing by to pick some up and make sure to eat it while it's hot!
Loved them, very authentic.
The chicken döner is to die for, don't miss the gem of a place. You'll keep going back.

As somebody born and raised in Germany, I always miss good Döner in the US.  Ali Baba delivered a great Döner, with organic poultry and fresh toppings. The bread was nice and crispy, the meat juicy and the garlic sauce very tasty!  Do expect to wait a while, but it’s worth it!
Food is great. Went two days in a row.

We got the döner sandwich with garlic sauce and spicy and it was sooooo delicious and tasty! We’ll definitely be going back. It was absolutely worth the wait while he made each sandwich to order. Sehr lecker!

The Doner is the best sandwhich in Chicago! Really small no frills place but great food!!!

WOW! If you miss having Doner from Europe then this is the spot for you!!!! The doner sandwich is extremely flavorful & fresh! Very filling. The place is really clean and modern on the inside. You can tell they use the best ingredients!! I’m so happy I found this gem! The man behind the counter was wearing gloves and a mask when preparing our food, definitely felt safe. Support local businesses during this hard time! We will be back for more doner!
I studied abroad in Germany for a year and have really missed German Turkish restaurants since I got back. This place is great!

I am native German and missed having a Doner! This place was randomly recommended by another fellow German and he assured me that this place is the real deal! I have been to many other places in Chicago that claimed that their Doner will taste exactly like the one in Germany but it was always a fail! Randomly one night I had a Doner craving and decided to drive to this Gem. The moment I walked in, I knew I was not going to be disappointed. I mean I was able to smell it and on top of everything the owners are German/Turkisch!  I am BIG into customer service and the owners of Ali Baba did not disappoint. We sat reminiscing about Germany and had amazing laughs! Their hospitality was beyond welcoming and the Doner was to die for! You can tell by the way they prepared the Doner that they take pride in what they do! All the ingredients were fresh and the meat was seasoned to perfection! There is not much more that I can say BUT seriously do yourself a favor, stop in and try one! You will thank me forever!
Its been a while I haven't had this good chicken doner.
Best doner sandwich in the city.

The only place I've found so far that captures the essence of the Doner Kebab. No, this isn't an American Kabob. This is an authentic Turkish Kebab. If you don't know what that is you NEED to try it from here. Amazing food and amazing service. 5/5 highly recommend.
Fantastic service and very delicious meals. Can't wait to go back!!!
a nice place to eat some turkish food. Iam from germany and its the same like here, i love it!

Hi there. This is not an advertising post, but rather a shout out to a place called Alibaba Doner in Lakeview. The place is owned by a German/Turkish gent who makes food fresh to order.  Not only is he super friendly, but the food is fresh, and amazing and extremely tasty.  The kicker: He makes cevaps with all the fixings, including a lepinja.  The reason of my shoutout...he's a good guy, the food is very reasonably priced and hits the spot each time.  Please give it a shot if you are in the neighborhood.  This is my facebook post
The Durum wrap took me right back to Rome! Loved this place. Also tried the traditional Doner sandwich and really loved the bread.

The food & service was 10/10! We had a Döner Sandwich and the Dürüm - fries combo and everything was fresh and tasty!! The place was very clean & topped off with Atalay‘s hospitality. We will definitely be back, Danke!!

The food is definitely worth the trip. I will be definitely coming back to Ali Baba Doner and getting my fix of traditional doner!!

Was so very impressed with this German donër!!!! I travel regularly and I was really craving one of these delicious kebabs and we are so glad we picked this place. The food was fresh, delicious, and wasn’t greasy. The owner was the biggest sweet heart from Germany to add to the authenticity!! Cute little shop perfect for a quick bite or take food to go. Turkish tea served for free which was a great gesture.  I recommend the donër sandwich and recommend ordering it spicy (it’s not too much heat), extra meat and extra garlic sauce to make it feel like you’re in Europe !! CAnt wait to Come back this was everything I needed. Danke!!!

I’ve been looking for a German-Turkish Döner place since visiting Austria and Germany. I fell in love with döner boxes and this is the first place I have found them in the US. The food here is definitely authentic and you can tell there is a lot of love and care put into it. The döner box with French fries is exactly what I’ve been looking for, so delicious. The meat and garlic sauce was flavorful and perfectly seasoned. The restaurant is IMMACULATE, after leaving that was the first thing my boyfriend and I commented on. To top it all off the man who owns the shop is so hospitable and is actually from Germany. I will be back and it is totally worth the 40 min commute to get there.

I was born and raised in Germany. I moved here a few years back and have yet to find a good German restaurant. Ali Baba’s Doner is a close as you can get to German Street food without actually going. If you’ve been to Germany or are German this WILL be your new favorite place. I’d give 30 stars if I could. The 10-15 minute wait is well worth the food. Please support this place with all you can.

One word. Incredible.  If you’re looking to grab a bite from a Mom & Pop shop, this is the place. Ali Baba Doner is ran by one man who puts his heart and soul into his food. Ali Baba Donor is a little gem that deserves your attention.  This is a smaller establishment that seats only about 8-10 people, but this is a prime example of how size doesn't matter.  The food was fantastic, and the owner/host was extremely helpful.  They were very conversational and seem to really enjoy serving people amazing food.  I would highly recommend this to anyone.  One interesting aspect was watching the owners assemble the food.  Through the glass panel I watched him meticulously layer each ingredient into the my sandwich; I was entranced.  He genuinely wanted the food to look as good as it tasted, and because he put the time into making it presentable - I think it really adds to the experience.  I will definitely be coming back.  The fries are an absolute must-try; some of the freshest I've had in a very long time. (No photo because I ate them too fast)  Fun fact: they speak English, Turkish and German!
Finally an authentic German Döner Place. You’ll get all the classics: Döner, Döner Box, Currywurst, Dürüm. As Austrian, I’m glad I finally found a great Döner place in the United States.

Please make sure you try this place, you won’t be disappointed.

This place is amazing! The owners really know how to make a fantastic doner. We were warmly welcomed in, offered a cozy seat, and some Turkish tea. I haven't had a doner this good since I visited Germany and ate them every day during my stay. So very excited to visit again!! Definitely a place to check out in Lincoln Park! Thank you so much!!
WOW! I Have been looking for a good Turkish Doner for years now! What a welcoming staff. Food was absolutely DELICIOUS!  Hope this place stays around for a long time!
Fantastic doners and great service. Will definitely be visiting regularly.

This place is absolutely amazing. I came back just few days after I tired it for the first time.  Doner is great. Turkish tea is awesome. Owner is nice and welcoming. I hope this place stays around for a long time.
The kebabs are deliciously flavorful and the owner is incredibly nice and helpful. I've already been back once and plan to make this a regular stop!
Kofta is amazing! Cooked to order 👌
Excellent spot for delicious Turkish food. Food was super flavorful. Prices are fair I would say.
Delicious food, excellent customer service. Do I need to say more? It’s the best doner in the city.

Amazing doner, really great seasoning. Also a good value and quick service. The owner is super nice and even gave us free Turkish tea while we were waiting. My husband and I plan to come here often for takeout dinners.
The owner was very friendly and the dorum doner was delicious!

Having been to similar Turkish establishments in Germany, this place is awesome! All the ingredients were fresh! I just had this for lunch and am seriously considering going back for dinner. Superb quality and service. The tea is delicious as well. Go here now!
The vegetarian sandwich and tea were very flavorful. The owner is exceptionally welcoming.
Been thinking about going since they opened, and now wish I'd gone sooner! Very good sandwiches and friendly owner.
I am really enjoying this little spot! The sandwiches are super fresh and the owner, Atalay, is very friendly. The food is made to order and worth the short wait!! Been back 3 times.
Great restaurant! I’m so glad I stopped and got lunch here. The chicken on my donor sandwich was DELICIOUS and the fries were excellent as well. I loved this place and will definitely be back.

I cannot stress enough how much EVERYONE needs to try this restaurant. The doner sandwich was made of chicken (with the owners homemade marinade) and so delicious, as well as red and green cabbage, raw onions, lettuce, garlic sauce, tomatoes and a bit of spice. French fries were very good, fresh and not too greasy. The owner is so kind, and made us Turkish Tea, which I had never had before. There is minimal seating, a few couches, but maybe they’ll add in more as time goes on. Good price for the quality. Come support this business! I will definitely be back time and time again.
Amazing food! Nice people. highly recomended
Great place if you want a taste of European street. Clean, owner is nice and polite, any problem going a bit off the menu :)
Absolutely delicious, and pretty unique if you’ve never had it before - definitely stop in. The owner makes your fries fresh just for you, and they are fantastic!
Excellent place, Nice people, great taste
Great place for a semi healthy and very tasty bite to eat. Chicken is tasty, all the veggies are fresh. I just wish there were a couple tables to sit down and eat my doner kebab at.
Never had a doner sandwich before. Amazing! Very clean place, fresh ingredients, and friendly family owned. A few free french fries for my toddler son as we waited. Support small business Diversey!

Just stopped in for lunch. The interior is so cozy! The owner told me it's not done yet. The doner sandwich I got was great and the fries were fresh right out of the fryer! I'll definitely be coming back for lunch. The owner is a super nice guy
The owner made me a delicious sandwich fresh while I waited the meat was outstanding I just wish they had some lamb options

This doner place just opened up today, February 20, 2019, and it's on my way home from the brown line so I stopped in for their opening deal (a doner sandwich--chicken with your choice of veggie toppings, traditional yogurt or garlic sauce, and spicy seasoning or feta cheese--and a can of soda for $9). The owners are super friendly and welcoming, and the doner was really tasty! There are a couple couches/benches to eat at inside but I think it will primarily be a takeout spot. Wishing them good luck, especially after all of the relatively recent business closures on this strip!
